The Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) CAPE TOWN – A 27-year-old police officer has been arrested on charges of culpable homicide and drunk-driving, after he allegedly hit a cyclist while driving a marked police vehicle.The Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) spokesperson Grace Langa confirmed they were investigating the case.“On Friday, February 4 at about 7pm, a motorist was driving a vehicle on the R59 towards Vanderbijlpark when he noticed a police marked van which was zig-zagging across the road. The police van took an off-ramp at the R42, and the motorist followed the police van because he said, ’the driver was driving recklessly’.”“On the corner of Andries Potgieter Street and Play Boulevard, the traffic lights turned red, but the police officer did not stop and the passenger of the motorist (witness) asked the officer to stop the van, because they could see that the (policeman) might cause an accident. “He then got out of his car and asked the police officer to give him his van’s keys so he (could) drive him to the nearest police station. The police officer refused to give him the keys and immediately drove off. As he was driving, the car hit an unknown African male who was riding a bicycle. “The police officer did not stop, but continued driving and the other driver (witness) followed him,” said Langa.Langa said the witness immediately reported the incident to the police and officers from Vanderbijlpark pursued the marked vehicle, and apprehend the police officer who is attached to the Vaal Marine visible policing unit based in Curie Boulevard.“He was arrested for drunk driving and a case of culpable homicide was also opened. The unknown male cyclist was certified dead on the scene,” Langa said. Cape Times